The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of weighted satisfiability problems on normalized circuits, which is a topic closely related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of genus as a parameter also suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves logical reasoning and proof complexity, which are topics in logic in computer science (cs.LO) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
